{
  "video_id": "VxE_itIllxE",
  "title": "The wonderful world of life in a drop of water | Tom Zimmerman and Simone Bianco",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12889.0,
      "end_time": 16230.0,
      "text": "Tom Zimmerman: We&#39;d like to take you on a fantastic journey"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16254.000000000002,
      "end_time": 18904.0,
      "text": "to visit the creatures we call the Elders."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19389.0,
      "end_time": 23363.0,
      "text": "We call them the Elders because a half a billion years ago"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 23387.0,
      "end_time": 26339.0,
      "text": "they tripled the amount of oxygen in the air,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26363.0,
      "end_time": 29291.0,
      "text": "which led to an explosion of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29315.0,
      "end_time": 30849.0,
      "text": "which led to all of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31670.0,
      "end_time": 35126.0,
      "text": "We call them the Elders, but you probably know them as plankton."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35631.0,
      "end_time": 36677.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36701.0,
      "end_time": 41110.0,
      "text": "Now, Simone is a physicist, and I&#39;m an inventor."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 41894.0,
      "end_time": 43700.0,
      "text": "A couple of years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43940.0,
      "end_time": 45341.0,
      "text": "I was giving a talk about an invention I made --"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 45365.0,
      "end_time": 46879.0,
      "text": "it was a 3D microscope."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46903.0,
      "end_time": 48807.0,
      "text": "And Simone was in the audience."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 49244.0,
      "end_time": 53478.0,
      "text": "He realized that my microscope could solve a big problem he was having."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 53861.0,
      "end_time": 58537.0,
      "text": "Which was, how to measure the movement of plankton in 3D fast enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 58561.0,
      "end_time": 62628.0,
      "text": "so he could mathematically model their sensing and behavior."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 63665.0,
      "end_time": 67407.0,
      "text": "And I frankly needed an application for my microscope, so ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 67431.0,
      "end_time": 68839.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 68863.0,
      "end_time": 70959.0,
      "text": "It was like peanut butter meets chocolate."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 70983.0,
      "end_time": 72395.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72419.0,
      "end_time": 76620.0,
      "text": "So we started working together, studying these amazing creatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 76489.0,
      "end_time": 79291.0,
      "text": "And then we were alarmed to discover something."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 79696.0,
      "end_time": 81809.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s why we&#39;re here today."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 81833.0,
      "end_time": 84206.0,
      "text": "And I just want to do something with you."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 84230.0,
      "end_time": 87166.0,
      "text": "Now, please, just hold your breath for a second."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 88470.0,
      "end_time": 89737.0,
      "text": "Yes, literally hold your breath."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89761.0,
      "end_time": 92761.0,
      "text": "This is the world without plankton."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 93161.0,
      "end_time": 97314.0,
      "text": "You see, plankton generate two-thirds of our oxygen using the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 97875.0,
      "end_time": 100336.0,
      "text": "OK, now you can breathe, because they&#39;re still here."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 101145.0,
      "end_time": 102295.0,
      "text": "For now."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 103458.0,
      "end_time": 105189.0,
      "text": "Simone Bianco: As many of you know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 105223.0,
      "end_time": 108228.0,
      "text": "since 1950, the average surface temperature of the earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 108252.0,
      "end_time": 110720.0,
      "text": "has increased by one degree Centigrade"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110744.0,
      "end_time": 113891.0,
      "text": "due to all the carbon dioxide we are pumping into the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 114784.0,
      "end_time": 118514.0,
      "text": "Now, while this temperature increase may not seem like a big deal to us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 118538.0,
      "end_time": 119926.0,
      "text": "it is to plankton."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 119950.0,
      "end_time": 124379.0,
      "text": "Indirect measurements have shown that the global phytoplankton population"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 124403.0,
      "end_time": 129465.0,
      "text": "may have decreased by as much as 40 percent between 1950 and 2010"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 129489.0,
      "end_time": 131600.0,
      "text": "because of climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 131300.0,
      "end_time": 132686.0,
      "text": "And you see, this is a problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 132710.0,
      "end_time": 136172.0,
      "text": "also because it&#39;s starving the fish that eat them."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 136196.0,
      "end_time": 138514.0,
      "text": "And about a billion people around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 138538.0,
      "end_time": 142505.0,
      "text": "depend on fish as their primary source of protein from animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 143109.0,
      "end_time": 145426.0,
      "text": "So you see, this isn&#39;t just about breathing."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 145792.0,
      "end_time": 147973.0,
      "text": "No plankton means no fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 147997.0,
      "end_time": 150458.0,
      "text": "And that is a lot of food we will need to replace."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 151117.0,
      "end_time": 153331.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s something else that is interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 153355.0,
      "end_time": 155458.0,
      "text": "The bodies of plankton&#39;s ancestors"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 155482.0,
      "end_time": 158377.0,
      "text": "actually make up a for lot of the carbon we burn today."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 158883.0,
      "end_time": 161600.0,
      "text": "Which is kind of ironic, if you ask me."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 161300.0,
      "end_time": 166228.0,
      "text": "Because the plankton that are here today clean that carbon out of the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 166252.0,
      "end_time": 168483.0,
      "text": "But you see, they don&#39;t really hold a grudge."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 168507.0,
      "end_time": 170850.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 170109.0,
      "end_time": 172578.0,
      "text": "The problem is they cannot keep up"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 172602.0,
      "end_time": 176302.0,
      "text": "with the tremendous amount of carbon we are dumping into the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 177930.0,
      "end_time": 178760.0,
      "text": "So what does all of this mean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 178784.0,
      "end_time": 181148.0,
      "text": "Well, it means that our big carbon footprint"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 181172.0,
      "end_time": 184446.0,
      "text": "is crushing the very creatures that sustain us."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 184784.0,
      "end_time": 186149.0,
      "text": "And yes, like Tom said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 186173.0,
      "end_time": 189164.0,
      "text": "killing almost half of the creatures that allow us to breathe"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 189188.0,
      "end_time": 190655.0,
      "text": "is a really big deal."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 191307.0,
      "end_time": 193291.0,
      "text": "So you&#39;re probably asking yourself:"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 193315.0,
      "end_time": 195384.0,
      "text": "Why aren&#39;t we doing something about it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 196900.0,
      "end_time": 199326.0,
      "text": "Our theory is that plankton are tiny,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 199350.0,
      "end_time": 202588.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s really, really hard to care about something you cannot see."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 203270.0,
      "end_time": 206664.0,
      "text": "You see, there&#39;s a quote I really like in \"The Little Prince\" that goes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 206688.0,
      "end_time": 209212.0,
      "text": "\"What is essential is invisible to the eye.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 209236.0,
      "end_time": 212459.0,
      "text": "We really believe that if more people could come"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 212483.0,
      "end_time": 216838.0,
      "text": "face to ... cilia with plankton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 216862.0,
      "end_time": 219394.0,
      "text": "there is a greater chance we could all rally together"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 219419.0,
      "end_time": 220594.0,
      "text": "and save these creatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 220618.0,
      "end_time": 222799.0,
      "text": "that are so important to life on our planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 222823.0,
      "end_time": 224355.0,
      "text": "TZ: Exactly, Simone."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 224379.0,
      "end_time": 225926.0,
      "text": "So to do this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 225950.0,
      "end_time": 230378.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to bring you scuba diving with plankton."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 231130.0,
      "end_time": 234641.0,
      "text": "But I just need to shrink you by a factor of 1000,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 234665.0,
      "end_time": 239109.0,
      "text": "to a scale where the diameter of a human hair is as big as my hand."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 239657.0,
      "end_time": 242815.0,
      "text": "And I happen to have invented a machine to do just that."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 243292.0,
      "end_time": 246609.0,
      "text": "SB: Anyone here remember \"Fantastic Voyage\""
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 246633.0,
      "end_time": 248290.0,
      "text": "or \"Innerspace?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 248387.0,
      "end_time": 249538.0,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 249562.0,
      "end_time": 253426.0,
      "text": "Martin Short is one of my all-time favorite actors."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 253450.0,
      "end_time": 256228.0,
      "text": "And now this -- this is just like that."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 256641.00000000003,
      "end_time": 257832.00000000003,
      "text": "TZ: Indeed, yes."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 257856.0,
      "end_time": 259885.0,
      "text": "When I was a boy, I saw \"Fantastic Voyage,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 259910.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263114.0,
      "text": "and I really loved how I could travel through the bloodstream"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 263138.0,
      "end_time": 266125.0,
      "text": "and see biology work on a cellular level."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 266149.0,
      "end_time": 268482.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve always been inspired by science fiction."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 268815.0,
      "end_time": 272349.0,
      "text": "As an inventor, I try and turn fantasy into reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 272966.0,
      "end_time": 275648.0,
      "text": "And I once invented this glove"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 275672.0,
      "end_time": 280268.0,
      "text": "which let me travel and help people like you explore the virtual world."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 280292.0,
      "end_time": 282133.0,
      "text": "So now I&#39;ve invented this machine"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 282157.0,
      "end_time": 285770.0,
      "text": "to let us explore the microscopic world."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 285101.0,
      "end_time": 287610.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not virtual, it&#39;s real."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 287850.0,
      "end_time": 288751.0,
      "text": "Just really, really tiny."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 289203.0,
      "end_time": 292155.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s based on the microscope that got Simone&#39;s attention."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 292180.0,
      "end_time": 293585.0,
      "text": "So, here&#39;s how it works."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 294434.0,
      "end_time": 296370.0,
      "text": "I have an image sensor"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 296394.0,
      "end_time": 299164.0,
      "text": "like the kind in your cell phone, behind the lens."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 299188.0,
      "end_time": 301656.0,
      "text": "And then I have a little tray of plankton water"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 301680.0,
      "end_time": 303428.0,
      "text": "like you might find from a river"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 303452.0,
      "end_time": 305887.0,
      "text": "or my fish tank, which I never change the water on."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 305911.0,
      "end_time": 307101.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 307125.0,
      "end_time": 308300.0,
      "text": "Because I love plankton."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 308324.0,
      "end_time": 311848.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 311872.0,
      "end_time": 314998.0,
      "text": "And underneath I have a light, an LED,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 315220.0,
      "end_time": 319420.0,
      "text": "which is going to cast shadows of the plankton on the image sensor."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 319887.0,
      "end_time": 322593.0,
      "text": "And now this silver thing is an XY plotter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 322617.0,
      "end_time": 326628.0,
      "text": "so I can move the image sensor to follow the plankton as they swim."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 327752.0,
      "end_time": 330461.0,
      "text": "Now comes the fantasy part."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 330485.0,
      "end_time": 331730.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 332141.0,
      "end_time": 335561.0,
      "text": "I put a tilt sensor on this helmet"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 335585.0,
      "end_time": 338652.0,
      "text": "so I can control the microscope with my head."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 339871.0,
      "end_time": 343640.0,
      "text": "And now let&#39;s look at the video from this image sensor."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 344466.0,
      "end_time": 346537.0,
      "text": "These are all plankton."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 346561.0,
      "end_time": 348482.0,
      "text": "This is in that little tray,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 348506.0,
      "end_time": 352893.0,
      "text": "and with my head, I can move the microscope."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 353212.0,
      "end_time": 356291.0,
      "text": "So now we&#39;re ready to go scuba diving with plankton."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 356807.0,
      "end_time": 359117.0,
      "text": "My head will be the navigator,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 359141.0,
      "end_time": 361290.0,
      "text": "and Simone will be our tour guide."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 361530.0,
      "end_time": 362204.0,
      "text": "SB: Yes."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 362228.0,
      "end_time": 363229.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 363253.0,
      "end_time": 367704.0,
      "text": "So welcome all to the wonderful world of life in a drop of water."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 367728.0,
      "end_time": 369330.0,
      "text": "Actually, as you can see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 369570.0,
      "end_time": 372786.0,
      "text": "with this instrument, we are not at all limited to a single drop."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 373106.0,
      "end_time": 374725.0,
      "text": "Alright, let&#39;s find something."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 375178.0,
      "end_time": 378320.0,
      "text": "The little creatures you see in the center of your screen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 378344.0,
      "end_time": 379836.0,
      "text": "they are called rotifer."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 379860.0,
      "end_time": 382418.0,
      "text": "They are the garbage collectors of our waters."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 382442.0,
      "end_time": 384498.0,
      "text": "They break down organic matter"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 384522.0,
      "end_time": 386966.0,
      "text": "and allow it to be reclaimed by the environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 387347.0,
      "end_time": 390402.0,
      "text": "Now, you know, nature is an amazing recycler."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 390427.0,
      "end_time": 394950.0,
      "text": "Structures are continuously built, they are decomposed and recycled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 394974.0,
      "end_time": 396997.0,
      "text": "and all of that is powered by solar energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 397403.0,
      "end_time": 398569.0,
      "text": "But just think."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 398593.0,
      "end_time": 402585.0,
      "text": "Think about what will happen if, you know, our garbage collectors"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 402609.0,
      "end_time": 405390.0,
      "text": "didn&#39;t come anymore, if they disappeared."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 405362.0,
      "end_time": 407505.0,
      "text": "Something else? Let&#39;s look for something else."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 407529.0,
      "end_time": 408689.0,
      "text": "Oh, look at that."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 408713.0,
      "end_time": 412102.0,
      "text": "You see the big ice-cream-cone-shaped things?"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 412126.0,
      "end_time": 415926.0,
      "text": "Those are called Stentor, those are amazing creatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 415950.0,
      "end_time": 418695.0,
      "text": "You know, they are big, but they are a single cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 418720.0,
      "end_time": 420910.0,
      "text": "You remember the rotifer we just met?"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 420934.0,
      "end_time": 424268.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s about half a millimeter, it&#39;s about 1,000 cells --"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 424292.0,
      "end_time": 428395.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s typically 15 for the brain, 15 for the stomach"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 428419.0,
      "end_time": 430609.0,
      "text": "and you know, about the same for reproduction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 430633.0,
      "end_time": 433195.0,
      "text": "which is kind of the right mix, if you ask me."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 433220.0,
      "end_time": 434221.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 434245.0,
      "end_time": 436920.0,
      "text": "But ... right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 436116.0,
      "end_time": 437279.0,
      "text": "TZ: I agree."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 437303.0,
      "end_time": 439553.0,
      "text": "SB: But a Stentor is only a single cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 439577.0,
      "end_time": 442268.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s able to sense and react to its environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 442292.0,
      "end_time": 445188.0,
      "text": "You see, it will swim forward when it&#39;s happy;"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 445212.0,
      "end_time": 448276.0,
      "text": "it will swim backward when it&#39;s trying to get away from something"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 448300.0,
      "end_time": 450322.0,
      "text": "like, you know, a toxic chemical."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 450713.0,
      "end_time": 453609.0,
      "text": "With our friends in the Center for Cellular Construction"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 453633.0,
      "end_time": 456680.0,
      "text": "and the help of the National Science Foundation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 456930.0,
      "end_time": 460641.0,
      "text": "we are using Stentor to sense the presence of contamination in food and water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 460665.0,
      "end_time": 462355.0,
      "text": "which I think is really cool."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 462379.0,
      "end_time": 463783.0,
      "text": "Alright, last one."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 463807.0,
      "end_time": 467503.0,
      "text": "So the dots that you see there that are, let&#39;s say, behind everything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 467527.0,
      "end_time": 468712.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re algae."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 468736.0,
      "end_time": 473409.0,
      "text": "They are the creatures that provide the majority of oxygen in the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 473434.0,
      "end_time": 476363.0,
      "text": "They convert solar light and carbon dioxide"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 476387.0,
      "end_time": 479188.0,
      "text": "into the oxygen that is filling your lungs right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 479212.0,
      "end_time": 481140.0,
      "text": "So you see, we all got algae breath."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 481165.0,
      "end_time": 482316.0,
      "text": "TZ: (Exhales)"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 482340.0,
      "end_time": 483933.0,
      "text": "SB: Yay! (Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 483958.0,
      "end_time": 485871.0,
      "text": "You know, there&#39;s something interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 485895.0,
      "end_time": 490933.0,
      "text": "About a billion years ago, ancient plants got their photosynthesis capability"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 490958.0,
      "end_time": 494671.0,
      "text": "by incorporating tiny, tiny plankton into their cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 494695.0,
      "end_time": 499188.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s exactly like us putting solar panels on top of our roofs."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 499212.0,
      "end_time": 503616.0,
      "text": "So you see, the microscopic world is even more amazing than science fiction."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 503641.0,
      "end_time": 504799.0,
      "text": "TZ: Oh, indeed."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 504823.0,
      "end_time": 508498.0,
      "text": "So now you&#39;ve seen how vital plankton are to our lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 508522.0,
      "end_time": 509982.0,
      "text": "and how much we need them."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 510418.0,
      "end_time": 513227.0,
      "text": "If we kill the plankton, we will die"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 513251.0,
      "end_time": 516219.0,
      "text": "of asphyxiation or starvation, take your pick."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 517720.0,
      "end_time": 519473.0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, I know it&#39;s sad, yes."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 519496.0,
      "end_time": 520925.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 520950.00000000006,
      "end_time": 524862.0,
      "text": "In the game of plankton, you win or you die."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 524886.0,
      "end_time": 527862.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 527886.0,
      "end_time": 533267.0,
      "text": "Now, what amazes me is, we have known about global warming"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 533292.0,
      "end_time": 535227.0,
      "text": "for over a century."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 535251.0,
      "end_time": 537949.0,
      "text": "Ever since the Swedish scientist, Arrhenius,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 537973.0,
      "end_time": 540617.0,
      "text": "calculated the effect of burning fossil fuel"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 540641.0,
      "end_time": 542275.0,
      "text": "on the earth&#39;s temperature."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 542299.0,
      "end_time": 546433.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve known about this for a long time, but it&#39;s not too late if we act now."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 547211.0,
      "end_time": 551450.0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, I know, I know, our world is based on fossil fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 551474.0,
      "end_time": 556450.0,
      "text": "but we can adjust our society to run on renewable energy from the Sun"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 556690.0,
      "end_time": 558664.0,
      "text": "to create a more sustainable and secure future."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 559930.0,
      "end_time": 561808.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s good for the little creatures here, the plankton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 561832.0,
      "end_time": 564320.0,
      "text": "and that good for us -- here&#39;s why."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 565770.0,
      "end_time": 568744.0,
      "text": "The three greatest concerns of people all around the globe"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 568768.0,
      "end_time": 571672.0,
      "text": "typically are jobs, violence and health."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 572379.0,
      "end_time": 574312.0,
      "text": "A job means food and shelter."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 574640.0,
      "end_time": 576925.0,
      "text": "Look at these creatures, they&#39;re swimming around,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 576950.0,
      "end_time": 579601.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re looking for a place to eat and reproduce."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 579990.0,
      "end_time": 582918.0,
      "text": "If a single cell is programmed to do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 582942.0,
      "end_time": 586774.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s no surprise that 30 trillion cells have the same agenda."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 588530.0,
      "end_time": 589203.0,
      "text": "Violence."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 589625.0,
      "end_time": 593781.0,
      "text": "Dependence on fossil fuels makes a country vulnerable."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 594195.0,
      "end_time": 599448.0,
      "text": "Which leads to conflicts all around the oil resources."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 600850.0,
      "end_time": 603903.0,
      "text": "Solar energy, on the other hand, is distributed around the whole globe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 603927.0,
      "end_time": 606572.0,
      "text": "and no one can blockade the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 606596.0,
      "end_time": 607966.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 607990.0,
      "end_time": 609682.0,
      "text": "And then, finally, health."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 610130.0,
      "end_time": 613367.0,
      "text": "Fossil fuels are like a global cigarette."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 613773.0,
      "end_time": 617660.0,
      "text": "And in my opinion, coal is like an unfiltered type."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 618305.0,
      "end_time": 622878.0,
      "text": "Now, just like smoking, the best time to quit is when?"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 622903.0,
      "end_time": 624690.0,
      "text": "Audience: Now."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 624930.0,
      "end_time": 625958.0,
      "text": "TZ: Now! Not when you get lung cancer."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 626513.0,
      "end_time": 632470.0,
      "text": "Now I know if you look around, some people may abandon facts and reason."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 632458.0,
      "end_time": 634156.0,
      "text": "Only until suffering --"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 634181.0,
      "end_time": 635182.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 635206.0,
      "end_time": 638530.0,
      "text": "Yes, they will abandon facts and reason."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 638770.0,
      "end_time": 643330.0,
      "text": "But suffering will eventually and inevitably force change."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 643354.0,
      "end_time": 647719.0,
      "text": "But let&#39;s instead use our neocortex, our new brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 647743.0,
      "end_time": 650822.0,
      "text": "to save the Elders, some of the oldest creatures on the earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 650846.0,
      "end_time": 654799.0,
      "text": "And let&#39;s apply science to harness the energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 654823.0,
      "end_time": 658352.0,
      "text": "that has fueled the Elders for millions of years --"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 659649.0,
      "end_time": 661320.0,
      "text": "the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 661560.0,
      "end_time": 662214.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 662238.0,
      "end_time": 665870.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}